apps/plugins/ -- contains no plugin, and no plugin code.

The plugin system was removed from this fork. The rb-> API struct, the .rock
loader, plugin_crt0.c, the plugin lib and every plugin source are gone. What is
left in this directory is here because something OUTSIDE apps/ names these
exact paths, and this fork's cleanup work is confined to apps/.

Do not "tidy up" this directory. Each file below breaks something if removed.

  plugin.lds
      *** STILL LIVE. NOT SCAFFOLDING. ***
      lib/rbcodec/codecs/codecs.make:168 sets
          CODEC_LDS := $(APPSDIR)/plugins/plugin.lds
      Codecs and plugins shared one linker script upstream. The plugins went
      away; the codecs did not. This script still links every .codec in the
      build. Delete or move it and codec linking breaks -- and it breaks late,
      at package time, not at compile time.

  plugins.make
  bitmaps/pluginbitmaps.make
      tools/root.make:134-135 `include`s both by exact path. A missing include
      (as opposed to -include) is a fatal make error. Both are inert.

  viewers.config
  CATEGORIES
      tools/buildzip.pl:497,550 open both with `or die`, so `make zip` fails
      outright if either is missing. Both are inert: CATEGORIES is a comment
      block, and the extension -> viewer map viewers.config used to carry was
      compiled into apps/filetypes.c in commit a86c1ab3fa.
      buildzip.pl is deliberately kept byte-identical to upstream (see
      CLAUDE.md); this fork's packaging lives in bundle-theme.sh instead.

  rockbox-fonts.config
      Copied by tools/buildzip.pl:590 into rocks/viewers/. Non-fatal if absent,
      but it is real content, so it stays.

  credits.pl
      Generates credits.raw from docs/CREDITS for the CORE credits screen
      (apps/credits.c). Nothing outside apps/ reads it, so this one is free to
      move -- and will, to apps/viewers/, in the apps/ reorganisation. The make
      rule that drives it already moved to apps/apps.make.

The whole directory can go the moment tools/ and lib/ become editable, and not
one file before then.

See .specifications/REFACTOR_PROPOSAL.md sections 3.1, 3.2 and 3.2a.
